      "description": "_nexus_pending() must check REVIEW_ISSUES count and block stop when count > 3",
      "type": "patterns_all_in_file",
      "path": "tools/HME/hooks/_nexus.sh",
      "patterns": [
        "REVIEW_ISSUES",
        "ri_count"
      ],
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "no-mcp-side-timeouts-synthesis",
      "description": "llama.cpp-backed synthesis must not enforce wall clocks MCP-side; timeout belongs in the llamacpp daemon. Lines inside _llamacpp_generate / _llamacpp_chat are exempt because llama.cpp has no persistent daemon \u2014 thread abandonment is the only way to enforce wall clocks on the OpenAI HTTP client.",
      "type": "shell_output_empty",
      "shell": "grep -n 'join(timeout=' tools/HME/mcp/server/tools_analysis/synthesis_llamacpp.py tools/HME/mcp/server/tools_analysis/synthesis_pipeline.py tools/HME/mcp/server/tools_analysis/evolution_suggest.py tools/HME/mcp/server/tools_analysis/workflow_audit.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v '# llamacpp-ok'",
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "lifesaver-todo-mirror-dedup",
      "description": "register_todo_from_lifesaver must dedupe by text+source so a monitor loop cannot flood the todo store with zombie entries (116 such entries polluted todos.json before this rule landed).",
      "type": "pattern_in_file",
      "path": "tools/HME/mcp/server/tools_analysis/todo.py",
      "pattern": "existing.get\\(.source.\\) == .lifesaver.",
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "no-hardcoded-llamacpp-ports",
      "description": "HME server files must not hardcode llamacpp ports 11434/11435/11436 \u2014 they were retired in commit 0577c0f7 when local inference moved to llama-server. Use HME_LLAMACPP_ARBITER_URL / HME_LLAMACPP_CODER_URL via os.environ, or the env fallback in the legacy llamacpp branch guarded by HME_ARBITER_BACKEND.",
      "type": "shell_output_empty",
      "shell": "grep -rnE 'localhost:1143[4-6]|127\\.0\\.0\\.1:1143[4-6]' tools/HME/mcp/server/ --include='*.py' | grep -v 'HME_LLAMACPP_PORT' | grep -v '# llamacpp-legacy-ok'",
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "conductor-no-or-zero-on-validator-output",
      "description": "Doubled fallback: `V.optionalFinite(x, N) || M` or `safePreBoot.call(fn, N) || M` is a dead outer fallback that also silently rewrites legitimate 0/false readings (see the regimeClassifierClassification 0\u21920.5 tension bug). Use the inner value directly, or nullish coalescing (??) if you want to catch only undefined.",
      "type": "shell_output_empty",
      "shell": "grep -rnE '(V\\.optionalFinite\\([^)]*,[^)]*\\)|safePreBoot\\.call\\([^)]*,[^)]*\\))\\s*\\|\\|' src/ --include='*.js'",
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "hme-py-exception-must-have-name",
      "description": "HME Python exception handlers must bind to `as _var` or named var so the type/message can be logged. Unbound `except Exception:` paired with anything other than `pass` (which is separately forbidden) is a code smell \u2014 you probably want to log the failure. Exempt: `except Exception: pass` is caught by hme-py-no-silent-catchall above; this rule catches the `except Exception:` + block-without-name case.",
      "type": "shell_output_empty",
      "shell": "python3 tools/HME/scripts/check-unnamed-except.py tools/HME/mcp/server",
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "conductor-histogram-uses-nullish",
      "description": "Map/object histogram counter reads should use `?? 0` not `|| 0`. A zero count in `(counts.get(k) || 0) + 1` is coerced to 0 + 1 \u2014 correct here \u2014 but the idiom is brittle; `?? 0` documents intent and won't break if the counter type changes to allow falsy non-undefined values.",
      "type": "shell_output_empty",
      "shell": "grep -rnE '\\.get\\([^)]*\\)\\s*\\|\\|\\s*0\\b' src/conductor/ --include='*.js' | grep -v '//.*nullish' | grep -v '\\.size'",
      "severity": "error"
    },
    {
      "id": "activity-emitter-exists",
      "description": "Phase 1 activity bridge (openshell_features_to_mimic.md) \u2014 shared event emitter CLI must exist so hooks can append to hme-activity.jsonl",
      "type": "file_exists",
      "path": "tools/HME/activity/emit.py",
      "severity": "error"
    },
